<dec f='qtbase-6.5.0/src/gui/kernel/qguiapplication.h' l='61' type='void QGuiApplication::setBadgeNumber(qint64 number)'/>
<def f='qtbase-6.5.0/src/gui/kernel/qguiapplication.cpp' l='763' ll='766' type='void QGuiApplication::setBadgeNumber(qint64 number)'/>
<doc f='qtbase-6.5.0/src/gui/kernel/qguiapplication.cpp' l='745'>/*!
    Sets the application&apos;s badge to \a number.

    Useful for providing feedback to the user about the number
    of unread messages or similar.

    The badge will be overlaid on the application&apos;s icon in the Dock
    on \macos, the home screen icon on iOS, or the task bar on Windows.

    If the number is outside the range supported by the platform, the
    number will be clamped to the supported range. If the number does
    not fit within the badge, the number may be visually elided.

    Setting the number to 0 will clear the badge.

    \since 6.5
    \sa applicationName
*/</doc>
